external_knowledge:
- The "fundamental measurements" refer to primary metrics in the context of these experiments; 
- The "specified model version" refers to the version 'v1.1' of the model with ID 1;
- The "crucial performance threshold" is a value of 0.9 for the primary metric being considered;
- "Associated experiments" indicate the experiments where these conditions were met.

sql:
SELECT AVG(version) AS average_version
FROM model_versions
WHERE version > 2.0;
